just_use detect.go

# label: SIMPLE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Retroactive trick attribution: given the hand cards a player released and
the board just before the move, return the trick ID that best explains
the move. Used by the CRUD replay view to annotate historical games that
never populated lynrummy_plays.

**Heuristic, not proof.** Matches on hand-card usage as a multiset, not
board-after byte equality. Ambiguity is possible in principle; DefaultOrder
(hand_stacks → direct_play → rb_swap → pair_peel → split_for_set →
peel_for_run → loose_card_play) gives a deterministic tiebreak that
matches TS's BAG. Sharpen later if real games show false attributions.
